Hi, This is not yet another of those routine profiles that u see, so read carefully on... 

Let me begin by mentioning something important here - 
It surprises me no end to find a lot of women boasting of different personal qualities like being simple, down to earth, understanding, loving, caring, smart, intelligent, good looking and so on and on and on... 
Well just a word of advice - No bloke is ever going to believe what u say about urself, unless he is low on intelligence. What matters is how he finds u after he gets to know u. No matter how u describe urself, its just ur photograph, age and social standing that almost always seals the initial decision to select u !! The rest of ur 'self-description' is simply ignored, or sometimes not even read !!! Thats just normal human tendency. The major part of the opinion about u is formed gradually in the course of interactions that follow. 
And then we have ladies who announce they prefer partners who r loving, understanding, caring, sensitive, smart, down to earth, friendly etc etc blah blah.. 
Well thats not a special, 'out- of- the- world' choice u've got -- thats what every woman is looking for, so u might as well just not mention it. 

now here's a few details about my turn of mind i'd urge u to consider before going for me :
I'd much rather have a woman reject me instantly than keep me waiting long. 
Its all very well to imagine that the slower the decision, the more sensible it is -- but the fact remains, that the quicker the decision, the more genuine and honest is the underlying attraction !! If u r not quick enough to decide on me, then either I dont deserve u, OR u r not worth waiting for ! [ usually, the former is true ! ] -- In most cases a slow decision is nothing but the process of trying to convince urself in someone's favour even though he may not be favourable ! Its never about how compatible we r before marriage but how we deal with incompatibility after. The fun lies in hitting it off inspite of differences, so think twice before u say that u want ur partner to be like this and like that. 

I stay with mom and dad in Andheri, Mumbai. 
Its a 2 bedroom apartment on the 5th floor. I have a pet dog called Robin. 
We have another 1 bedroom apt. just a few minutes away which is currently rented out. 

Just took a bit long sorting out my career, which is firmly in place now - so marriage plans had to be held back. 

I reserve the highest passion for clothes, perfumes and watches - my eternal weakness ( although those will have to make way for 'Miss Right' !! ) 
I cant resist material pleasures and stop at nothing to buy anything that catches my fancy. 

Im not the highly ambitious sort - i've never been - 
Its a little tricky to set ambitions and go after it when u're too busy
enjoying life ! 

My prized possession today is the unforgettable scent of a perfume gifted to me years ago. Memories of the gifter have long faded away but somewhere deep inside me, the fragrance still lingers on !!

About my eating habits- I have a racing appetite for food, and prefer home food, like those cooked by mom and sis - 
I'd rather starve than eat junk food, but I do have a sweet tooth, infact not just one, but around 32 sweet teeth !! I just gobble up whatever sweet i can lay my hands on. [ So, i dont want my wife to be too sweet ! ]

The almighty has always showered me with THE BEST in this world... 
So i hope THE BEST WIFE is on her way too !!!
=========================================
1 final point -
All u ladies with a tendency to make a show of ur 'care less' attitude by taking ur own time to respond to messages etc, or on the pretext of being too busy blah blah blah --
As much as ur style impresses me, please.. KEEP AWAY ! 

The rest of u - simple, graceful, unpretentious gentlewomen, 
U have my highest welcome. 
Cheers
